YOLA – Son of a retired Naval Admiral and one time Chief of Navy Staff, Admiral Murtala Nyako, Sen Abdulaziz Nyako has coasted to victory winning the APC Adamawa central ticket, defeating Ahmed Musa and Dr. Umar Bindir in a landslide victory. Aziz Nyako who took his APC opponents down in a swift stake won Adamawa central ticket with ease. Senator Abdulaziz Murtala Nyako who emerged winner of the All Progressives Congress senatorial primaries election for Adamawa central senatorial zone was elated. -Advertisement- Declaring Nyako the winner of the contest, the Chairman primary election committee, Dr. Muazu Shehu said, Nyako won the contest after polling 292 votes. According to the chairman of the electoral committee, the first runner-up, of the election, Abdullahi Musa, polled 72 votes, while Dr. Umar Bindir got 13 votes.The election also recorded two invalid votes while a total of 379 votes were casted. With this outcome, Nyako will face the incumbent speaker of Adamawa State House of assembly Aminu Iya Abbas who emerged as the flagbearer of the People’s Democratic Party (PDP), Adamawa central senatorial zone in the general election come 2023. Aziz is said to be battle ready to crush his PDP opponent Iya Abbas, speaker State House of Assembly who got the PDP ticket in a controversial manner for the Central Senatorial seat. Aziz’s strongest contenders where trounced as the son of Admiral Murtala Nyako cleared the first huddles for his 2023 Senate race.